WEBVTT

00:01.130 --> 00:03.360
(radio static crackles)

00:03.400 --> 00:05.197
WHERE IS IT?
(female dispatcher)
Suspect is armed and dangerous.

00:05.230 --> 00:07.437
His name--Kevin Michael Ford.
ALL YOUR CARS HAVE THEM.

00:07.470 --> 00:08.960
42 years old.
WHERE IS IT?

00:09.000 --> 00:11.605
Currently resides
at 30 Furlough Street.
(lock clicks, trunk door
squeaks)

00:11.640 --> 00:14.074
(trunk door clunks)
Wanted for the shooting
of Officer Chloe Price.

00:14.110 --> 00:17.307
(ALT-J's "Tessellate" playing)

00:17.350 --> 00:21.377
* BITE CHUNKS OUT OF ME

00:21.420 --> 00:24.309
* YOU'RE A SHARK,
AND_I'M SWIMMING *
(radio statIc crackles)

00:24.350 --> 00:28.753
(clatters)
* MY HEART STILL THUMPS
AS I BLEED *

00:28.790 --> 00:30.280
(back seat thuds)
* ALL YOUR FRIENDS

00:30.330 --> 00:32.457
* COME SNIFFING
(clanks and thuds)

00:32.500 --> 00:36.618
OKAY.
* TRIANGLES
ARE MY FAVORITE SHAPE *

00:36.670 --> 00:40.060
(clunks and rattles)
OKAY. HERE WE GO.

00:40.100 --> 00:41.431
(faint thud in distance)
THIS IS GONNA BE GOOD.

00:41.470 --> 00:44.064
* TOE-TO-TOE, BACK-TO-BACK
(grunts and sighs)

00:44.110 --> 00:45.134
* LET'S GO
NO.

00:45.170 --> 00:48.333
(grunting)
SERIOUSLY.
THIS IS GOING TO BE GOOD.

00:48.380 --> 00:49.699
(punche
s
UHH! )

00:49.750 --> 00:51.399
* 'TIL MORNING COMES
(trunk door squeaks, thuds)

00:54.280 --> 00:55.611
* LET'S TESSELLATE

00:55.650 --> 00:58.642
-- Captions by VITA --

00:58.690 --> 01:00.453
ALL RIGHT.
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME

01:00.490 --> 01:02.720
YOU SAW KEVIN FORD?
TWO WEEKS AGO.

01:02.760 --> 01:04.352
THE NIGHT BEFORE HIS NEIGHBOR
BEAT HIM UP.

01:04.390 --> 01:05.789
AND YOU HAVE NOT
SEEN HIM SINCE?

01:05.830 --> 01:07.525
NOT TODAY? NOT YESTERDAY?

01:07.560 --> 01:08.356
YOU HAVEN'T
DRIVEN BY HIS HOUSE

01:08.400 --> 01:10.220
OR CHECKED UP ON HIM
AT THE HOSPITAL?

01:10.270 --> 01:12.238
SAM,
I SAID I HAVEN'T SEEN HIM.

01:12.270 --> 01:14.488
(cell phone beeps)

01:14.540 --> 01:16.405
HEY, WHAT'S UP?
YOU'RE NOT GONNA LIKE IT.

01:16.440 --> 01:18.431
(scoffs) I CAN'T STAND IT
WHEN YOU OPEN WITH THAT.

01:18.470 --> 01:20.529
DON'T OPEN WITH THAT.
MCNALLY?

01:20.580 --> 01:22.377
(radio chatter)
HIT ME.

01:22.410 --> 01:24.708
I'M IN MARLO'S BASEMENT.
IT'S ALL KEVIN FORD.

01:24.750 --> 01:28.641
MAPS, PHOTOGRAPHS, NOTES,
CHARTS. IT'S...

01:28.680 --> 01:30.284
(sighs) IT'S CRAZY.

01:30.320 --> 01:32.584
Andy she must have been
following this guy for weeks.

01:32.620 --> 01:35.714
LOOK, NO ONE'S SEEN IT YET.

01:35.760 --> 01:38.251
I'M STILL WAITING ON OLIVER.
Okay.

01:38.290 --> 01:41.589
JUST KEEP ME POSTED.

01:41.630 --> 01:43.325
WHAT?

01:45.800 --> 01:46.892
MARLO, I THINK WE NEED
TO TALK ABOUT

01:46.940 --> 01:48.089
WHAT'S IN YOUR BASEMENT.

01:51.470 --> 01:54.234
(radio static)
THIS IS 1527.
I'M STILL WAITING ON BACKUP.

01:54.280 --> 01:55.679
1504, WHAT'S YOUR 20?

01:55.710 --> 01:57.803
(horn blares in distance)

01:57.850 --> 02:01.240
(radio static)
1504, ALMOST THERE.

02:01.280 --> 02:02.417
You okay?
(radio static)

02:02.450 --> 02:03.917
YEAH. YEAH I'M--I'M FINE.

02:03.950 --> 02:07.386
GOOD. SEE YOU SOON.
(radIo static)

02:07.420 --> 02:09.320
(walkie-talkie clicks)

02:09.360 --> 02:12.329
(woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A.)

02:12.360 --> 02:15.818
(telephone rings in distance)

02:15.860 --> 02:17.760
THANK YOU.
RIGHT ON.

02:17.800 --> 02:19.563
(siren wails in distance,
monitor beeping rhythmically)

02:19.600 --> 02:20.897
(coffee lid clicks)

02:20.940 --> 02:23.329
LISTEN, WES, THERE'S
SOMETHING I NEED TO TELL YOU.

02:24.710 --> 02:28.305
CHLOE AND I ARE, UM...
SEEING EACH OTHER.

02:28.340 --> 02:31.241
(scoffs)
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY SO?

02:31.280 --> 02:32.076
WELL, 'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,

02:32.110 --> 02:33.418
THIS WHOLE THING
CAUGHT ME OFF GUARD.

02:33.450 --> 02:34.917
I DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT YOU.

02:34.950 --> 02:36.611
AND I DIDN'T KNOW
SHE'D BEEN MARRIED.

02:36.650 --> 02:38.641
NOT SURE IF THAT SAYS
MORE ABOUT

02:38.690 --> 02:41.887
MY RELATIONSHIP
WITH HER OR YOURS.
YEAH. ME NEITHER.

02:41.920 --> 02:45.424
IS IT SERIOUS--
YOU AND HER?

02:48.260 --> 02:50.820
YEAH.
YOU HAD TO THINK ABOUT IT.
YOU SURE?

02:50.870 --> 02:52.235
YEAH, BECAUSE THIS IS WEIRD.
OKAY?

02:52.270 --> 02:53.396
I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOU.
AND--AN D--AN D--AND--

02:53.440 --> 02:55.635
YOU'RE--YOU'RE ASKING ME
IF I'M SERIOUS--

02:55.670 --> 02:57.365
IF--ABOUT--
MY WIFE.

02:57.410 --> 03:00.937
EXACTLY. SO, YES, WES,
I'M VERY INTO YOUR WIFE.

03:00.980 --> 03:02.641
YOUR WIFE AND I
ARE GOING STEADY.

03:02.680 --> 03:06.275
(scoffs) YOU MAKE HER HAPPY?

03:06.320 --> 03:07.844
I THINK SO.

03:07.880 --> 03:10.246
YOU HAD TO THINK
ABOUT IT AGAIN.
WELL, YOU'RE IMPATIENT.

03:10.290 --> 03:12.417
I'M JUST TRYING TO GAUGE
WHAT I'M UP AGAINST.

03:16.430 --> 03:18.955
(door buzzes,
indistinct conversations)

03:18.990 --> 03:20.924
(telephone ringing in distance,
radio chatter)

03:20.960 --> 03:24.259
WHAT'S HAPPENING?
FORD'S LAWYER JUST GOT HERE.

03:24.300 --> 03:25.824
WHAT'S THAT MEAN?
(beeps)

03:25.870 --> 03:27.462
IT'S THE USUAL, YOU KNOW,
YOU GUYS GOT IT ALL WRONG.

03:27.500 --> 03:30.264
MY CLIENT'S A GREAT GUY,
HE LOVES PUPPIES. HE'S INNOCENT.

03:30.310 --> 03:31.959
MY CLIENT
IS OUT OF HIS MIND.

03:32.010 --> 03:34.570
UH, FORMER CLIENT,
I SHOULD SAY.

03:34.610 --> 03:35.702
KEVIN CALLED ME
INTO THE HOSPITAL,

03:35.740 --> 03:38.846
SAID HE WANTED TO FILE
A LAWSUIT AGAINST THE POLICE.

03:38.880 --> 03:42.543
HE CLAIMED THAT YOU GUYS WERE
PERSECUTING HIM, FOLLOWING HIM,

03:42.590 --> 03:44.683
FRAMING HIM FOR CRIMES
HE DIDN'T COMMIT.

03:44.720 --> 03:46.859
BUT WHEN I TOLD HIM
THAT IT WOULD TAKE A FEW WEEKS

03:46.890 --> 03:49.552
TO LOOK AT THE FACTS,
HE ATI'ACKED ME.

03:49.590 --> 03:52.024
IT TOOK TWO NURSES
TO GET HIM OFF ME.

03:52.060 --> 03:55.393
WHY DIDN'T YOU REPORT IT?

03:55.430 --> 03:57.762
I WAS AFRAID HE WAS
GOING TO COME AFTER ME.

03:57.800 --> 04:00.337
LOOK, I HAVE WORKED
WITH KEVIN FOR A WHILE,

04:00.370 --> 04:01.860
AND HE'S ALWAYS BEEN
A BIT OF A LONER.

04:01.900 --> 04:04.937
BUT THIS WAS INSANE.
WHAT DID THE HOSPITAL SAY?

04:04.970 --> 04:07.768
THEY SAID HE HAD SUFFERED
A TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY.

04:07.810 --> 04:11.803
ERRATIC BEHAVIOR, PARANOIA,
TROUBLE WITH IMPULSE CONTROL.

04:11.850 --> 04:14.341
SO HE THINKS HE'S BEING
PERSECUTED BY THE POLICE.

04:14.380 --> 04:17.019
NOW ANYONE IN PARTICULAR?
YEAH. 15 DIVISION.

04:17.050 --> 04:20.611
HE SAID HE WASN'T GONNA STOP
UNTIL IT WAS OVER.

04:20.660 --> 04:23.049
OKAY, LISTEN UP.

04:23.090 --> 04:25.957
AS MOST OF YOU KNOW,
WE BELIEVE OUR SHOOTER TO BE

04:25.990 --> 04:28.823
ONE KEVIN FORD, 42 YEARS OLD,
CAUCASIAN MALE,

04:28.860 --> 04:30.964
SUFFERING FROM
A SEVERE TRAUMATIC BRAIN INJURY.

04:31.000 --> 04:33.594
FORMER SUSPECT IN
A MISSING CHILD INVESTIGATION.

04:33.640 --> 04:34.664
WE GOT OFFICERS
AT HIS WORKPLACE,

04:34.700 --> 04:36.361
AND A B.O.L.O. OUT ON HIS VAN.

04:36.410 --> 04:38.628
UNIFORMS ARE AT FORD'S HOUSE.
IT'S EMPTY. HE'S NOT THERE.

04:38.670 --> 04:40.308
ALL RIGHT. WE'LL GET OVER
AND CHECK IT OUT.

04:40.340 --> 04:42.877
HIS PARENTS ARE DECEASED.
WE NEED TO FIND HIS BROTHER.

04:42.910 --> 04:46.846
ABE FORD, 50 YEARS OLD,
673 PARKSIDE ROAD.

04:46.880 --> 04:49.815
PECK, DIAZ... BRING HIM IN.
KEEP IT FRIENDLY.

04:49.850 --> 04:50.942
WE'RE ON IT.

04:50.990 --> 04:51.740
ALL RIGHT. THE REST OF YOU,

04:51.790 --> 04:53.678
I WANT YOU OUT ON PATROL
IN PAIRS.

04:53.720 --> 04:54.789
OKAY, WE'RE LOOKING FOR
A WHITE PANEL VAN.

04:54.820 --> 04:56.287
THE PLATE NUMBER'S
ON THE HANDOUT.

04:56.330 --> 04:59.493
AND BE CAREFUL OUT THERE.
GOOD TO SEE YOU, OFFICER.
GLAD YOU'RE SAFE.

04:59.530 --> 05:02.658
NICK'S AT HER HOUSE RIGHT NOW.
ALL RIGHT.
WE'LL SEND FORENSICS OVER.

05:02.700 --> 05:04.065
SWAREK, YOU GOOD TO TAKE
HER STATEMENT?

05:04.100 --> 05:05.465
YEAH, YEAH, WE'RE GOOD.

05:07.740 --> 05:09.708
OKAY, WE HAVE
TO EXPLAIN THIS TO THEM.

05:09.740 --> 05:11.503
EXPLAIN WHAT?
THERE'S NOTHING WE CAN DO.

05:11.540 --> 05:12.734
THEY'RE GOING TO FIND
EVERYTHING NOW.

05:19.650 --> 05:23.381
TAKE IT EASY. ALL RIGHT?

05:23.420 --> 05:26.048
MOM WOULD KILL ME
IF ANYTHING HAPPENS TO YOU.
YEAH. PLEASE.

05:26.090 --> 05:27.159
SHE WOULDN'T EVEN NOTICE.

05:27.190 --> 05:30.125
(zips bag)
DON'T WORRY, DETECTIVE.
I GOT HER BACK.

05:30.160 --> 05:31.752
ALWAYS HAVE, ALWAYS WILL.

05:31.790 --> 05:32.927
GAIL.

05:32.960 --> 05:34.928
HOLLY, HEY.

05:34.960 --> 05:36.120
HI.

05:36.160 --> 05:38.060
HEY.
YOU SAID THAT ALREADY.

05:38.100 --> 05:40.091
YOU KNOW,
IT SOUNDED FAMILIAR.

05:40.140 --> 05:42.096
I JUST WANTED TO SEE YOU.

05:42.140 --> 05:44.836
YOU KNOW, TAKE TEN MINUTES,
LAY EYES ON YOU.

05:44.870 --> 05:47.100
(radio chatter)

05:47.140 --> 05:49.847
OH. OKAY, SO THAT'S
HOW WE'RE GONNA DO THIS.

05:49.880 --> 05:52.576
MM-HMM.
GAIL, WE SHOULD PROBABLY
GET GOING.

05:52.620 --> 05:55.646
JUST...
JUST BE CAREFUL, OKAY?

05:55.680 --> 05:57.716
I WILL.

06:02.730 --> 06:05.824
(indistinct conversations,
telephone ringing in distance)

06:05.860 --> 06:07.953
SO EVERYTHING IN YOUR HOUSE
IS NOW EVIDENCE.

06:08.000 --> 06:11.458
I SHOULD HAVE PACKED IT UP.
BURNED IT.

06:11.500 --> 06:13.092
I WASN'T THINKING STRAIGHT.
YOU KNOW THAT.

06:13.140 --> 06:17.736
LOOK, THE, UH,
SILVER LINING IS THAT--

06:17.770 --> 06:19.829
THAT YOU KNOW MORE ABOUT
THIS GUY THAN ANYONE ELSE.

06:19.880 --> 06:21.836
OKAY, SO LET'S START
THINKING ABOUT THAT.
(folder slides)

06:21.880 --> 06:24.747
WHAT DO YOU WE KNOW?
YOU HEARD FROM OLIVER?

06:24.780 --> 06:27.010
NO. WHY?
'CAUSE HE STILL HASN'T SHOWN UP.

06:27.050 --> 06:28.039
NICK CAN'T REACH HIM.

06:28.080 --> 06:29.684
CELERY HASN'T HEARD FROM HIM.

06:29.720 --> 06:31.039
I JUST TRIED TO CALL HIM
THREE TIMES,

06:31.090 --> 06:32.785
AND HIS CELL PHONE IS OFF.
WHAT DOES DISPATCH SAY?

06:32.820 --> 06:34.515
APPARENTLY HE'S BEEN PARKED
IN THE SAME LOCATION

06:34.560 --> 06:36.949
FOR THE LAST 45 MINUTES.
3900 LAKE SHORE.

06:36.990 --> 06:39.697
I'LL BE HERE.

06:39.730 --> 06:42.051
THIS IS 1519.
THERE'S NO CAR HERE.

06:42.100 --> 06:43.795
CAN YOU PLEASE REPEAT
THE LOCATION?
(radIo static)

06:43.830 --> 06:45.889
(female dispatcher)
GPS On car 1504 still reads

06:45.930 --> 06:48.569
3900 Lake Shore.
OKAY. WELL THERE IS NO
3900 LAKE SHORE.

06:48.600 --> 06:51.706
I MEAN, IT'S AN EMPTY LOT.
ANDY.

06:51.740 --> 06:54.106
1519, we're trying
to narrow it down.
(radIo static)

06:54.140 --> 06:56.199
WE FOUND IT.
WE FOUND THE SENDER UNIT.

06:56.240 --> 06:57.946
IT'S BEEN TAKEN
OUT OF THE CAR.

06:57.980 --> 07:01.472
Sorry, go again.
You found the car?
NO, WE FOUND THE BOX.

07:01.520 --> 07:02.919
THE CAR IS MISSING.

07:02.950 --> 07:07.614
THERE'S NO SIGN
OF OFFICER SHAW.

07:07.660 --> 07:10.629
(radio chatter, siren wailing)

07:13.630 --> 07:16.667
(indistinct conversations,
camera shutter clicks)

07:16.700 --> 07:18.122
FINAL ACT PREPARATIONS.

07:18.170 --> 07:19.797
HE TURNED DOWN THE HEAT,
PAID HIS BILLS,

07:19.840 --> 07:21.091
EVEN LAID HIS SUIT OUT.

07:21.140 --> 07:22.835
THIS WAS TAPED
TO HIS COMPUTER.

07:22.870 --> 07:24.929
(camera shutter clicking)

07:24.970 --> 07:27.734
"MARLO CRUZ, SAM SWAREK,
OLIVER SHAW...

07:27.780 --> 07:31.841
ANDY, CHLOE, DOV, NICK."

07:31.880 --> 07:34.940
YEAH. IT'S A HIT LIST.

07:37.590 --> 07:42.050
(sirens wailing,
helicopter whirring)

07:42.090 --> 07:45.025
(radio chatter)

07:46.930 --> 07:48.795
LAST RADIO CONTACT WAS
39 MINUTES AGO.

07:48.830 --> 07:50.718
OLIVER SAID HE WAS
ON HIS WAY HERE.

07:50.770 --> 07:51.794
SO WHAT, HE NEVER SHOWED?

07:51.830 --> 07:53.263
HE DID. HIS UNIT LOCATOR
PINGED HIM AT THIS ADDRESS

07:53.300 --> 07:54.995
ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.
IF HE'D ALREADY BEEN HERE,

07:55.040 --> 07:57.167
WHY DID HE SAY HE WAS
ON HIS WAY?
(Siren whoops)

07:57.210 --> 07:58.666
OKAY, GOT IT.
(cell phone beeps)

07:58.710 --> 08:00.803
THE GUYS JUST FOUND
FORD'S VAN AROUND THE CORNER.

08:00.840 --> 08:03.946
WHAT ABOUT OLIVER'S CELL?
THERE'S NO SIGNAL.

08:03.980 --> 08:05.709
THEY GOT TECHS
WORKING ON THE VAN,

08:05.750 --> 08:07.047
UNIFORMS ARE SEARCHING
THE PARK.

08:07.080 --> 08:09.048
FOR WHAT? A BODY?

08:09.080 --> 08:11.617
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
DETECTIVE...

08:11.650 --> 08:13.117
THERE'S SOMETHING
I THINK YOU NEED TO SEE.

08:14.990 --> 08:16.924
HEY, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
YOU TWO...

08:16.960 --> 08:17.927
LOOK,
AS SOON AS WE'RE DONE HERE,

08:17.960 --> 08:18.756
I WANT YOU BACK AT THE STATION.

08:18.790 --> 08:20.189
YOU STAY THERE
UNTIL THIS IS OVER.

08:20.230 --> 08:21.629
WHAT?
WHY?

08:21.660 --> 08:23.525
FRANK, THIS IS OLIVER.
WE NEED TO BE IN THIS.

08:23.570 --> 08:26.630
KEVIN FORD MADE A HIT LIST,
SAM, AND YOU'RE ON IT.

08:26.670 --> 08:30.128
SO IS MCNALLY, SO IS CHLOE,
WHO'S NOW IN I.C.U.

08:30.170 --> 08:32.001
SO IS OLIVER,
WHO'S NOW MISSING.

08:32.040 --> 08:33.735
SO UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE,

08:33.780 --> 08:35.077
YOU'RE BOTH STAYING
AT THE DAMN STATION.

08:35.110 --> 08:38.773
(helicopter whirring,
siren wailing)

08:42.950 --> 08:44.815
(radio chatter)

08:44.850 --> 08:45.942
WHAT IS THIS?

08:45.990 --> 08:47.912
LOOKS LIKE MARLO
WAS DOING HER RESEARCH.

08:47.960 --> 08:50.326
SHE'S GOT COPIES OF EVERY FILE
ON KEVIN FORD,

08:50.360 --> 08:53.295
EVERY INTERVIEW WITH HIM,
ABOUT HIM.

08:53.330 --> 08:54.854
IT STRETCH ES BACK ABOUT
TH REE YEARS.

08:54.900 --> 08:56.561
THERE'S EVEN A TIMELINE.

08:56.600 --> 08:58.921
WHY AREN'T THESE CONFIDENTIAL
FILES BACK AT THE STATION?

08:58.970 --> 09:01.234
(radio chatter)

09:01.270 --> 09:04.000
YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:04.040 --> 09:06.838
MARLO HAD A HUNCH.
CLEARLY SHE WAS RIGHT.

09:06.880 --> 09:09.678
EXCUSE ME?

09:09.710 --> 09:13.214
LUKE... SHE SLIPPED UP,

09:13.250 --> 09:17.584
BUT SHE'S BACK ON HER MEDS.
SHE'S--SHE'S BE'I'I'ER NOW.

09:17.620 --> 09:19.611
MEDS FOR WHAT?

09:19.660 --> 09:22.151
(siren wailing in distance)
MEDS FOR WHAT?!

09:22.190 --> 09:24.624
SHE'S BIPOLAR.

09:24.660 --> 09:27.857
SHE HAD A MANIC EPISODE--
JUST A BREAK.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.822
SO SHE ENDED UP FOCUSING
ALL OF HER ENERGY

09:29.870 --> 09:31.223
INTO KEVIN FORD
BECAUSE SHE THINKS

09:31.270 --> 09:33.329
THAT HE KILLED THE KID
TH REE YEARS AGO.

09:33.370 --> 09:34.928
YOU BOTH HAVE BEEN COVERING
FOR HER?

09:34.970 --> 09:37.734
SHE WAS RIGHT.
OKAY, SHE WAS RIGHT.

09:37.770 --> 09:39.135
LOOK AT WHERE WE ARE.
LOOK AT WHAT HE'S DOING.

09:39.170 --> 09:41.206
(laughs)
SHE WAS DEAD RIGHT
ABOUT THE GUY.

09:41.240 --> 09:44.346
YEAH. OH.

09:44.380 --> 09:45.779
BOX IT UP.
BRING IT TO THE STATION.

09:45.810 --> 09:47.778
MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING
WE CAN USE.
LUKE--

09:47.820 --> 09:49.139
I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU
ABOUT THIS RIGHT NOW.

09:49.180 --> 09:51.148
WE HAVE AN (ID-[FJFICER MISSING.

09:51.190 --> 09:53.886
(siren wailing in distance)

09:53.920 --> 09:54.909
SO HOW DOES THIS WORK?

09:54.960 --> 09:56.621
WE WAIT FOR HER TO WAKE UP,
AND THEN WE DUEL?

09:56.660 --> 09:59.254
(chuckles) GUNS OR KNIVES?

09:59.290 --> 10:00.723
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT PUB TRIVIA?

10:00.760 --> 10:03.627
YOU MUST BE
MISS PRICE'S HUSBAND.

10:03.670 --> 10:06.230
CAN I HAVE A WORD?
UH, ACTUALLY,
I'M HER HUSBAND.

10:06.270 --> 10:10.138
OH, OKAY. A-AND YOU ARE?
BOYFRIEND.

10:10.170 --> 10:12.104
(P.A. tone chimes,
woman speaking indistinctly)
EVERYTHING OKAY?

10:12.140 --> 10:14.802
UNFORTUNATELY,
THE LATEST C.T. SHOWS

10:14.840 --> 10:16.876
A CLOT IN HER CAROTID ARTERY,

10:16.910 --> 10:18.878
WHERE WE REPAIRED
THE GUNSHOT WOUND.

10:18.910 --> 10:20.138
AND I THINK
WE SHOULD REMOVE IT.

10:20.180 --> 10:22.114
WE'VE GOT A WINDOW
OF OPPORTUNITY HERE,

10:22.150 --> 10:23.082
AND IF WE LEAVE IT,

10:23.120 --> 10:25.213
I'M CONCERNED THAT SHE COULD
SUFFER A STROKE,

10:25.250 --> 10:27.855
NEUROLOGICAL DAMAGE,
POSSIBLY EVEN PARALYSIS.

10:27.890 --> 10:30.154
SO... WHAT ARE WE
WAITING FOR?

10:30.190 --> 10:32.920
AS WITH EVERY PROCEDURE,
THERE ARE RISKS,

10:32.960 --> 10:34.291
AND YOU SHOULD KNOW
WHAT THEY ARE.

10:34.330 --> 10:35.228
RISKS? WHAT KIND OF RISKS?

10:35.260 --> 10:37.797
WE'LL NEED TO CLAMP OFF
THE DAMAGED ARTERY

10:37.830 --> 10:39.661
TO GET TO THE CLOT.

10:39.700 --> 10:41.895
PROBLEM IS SHE HAS SWELLING
ON THE OTHER SIDE.

10:41.940 --> 10:44.431
IF THAT SWELLING INCREASES
WHILE WE'RE OPERATING,

10:44.470 --> 10:45.937
THERE'S A POSSIBILITY

10:45.970 --> 10:47.301
THAT SHE MIGHT NOT GET
SUFFICIENT CIRCULATION,

10:47.340 --> 10:48.876
WHICH COULD LEAD TO BRAIN DEATH.

10:48.910 --> 10:52.710
HOW MUCH OF A POSSIBILITY?
I'D SAY IT'S UNLIKELY.

