NO, I'M SERIOUS.
I'M SERIOUS. YOU MADE YOUR LIST.

22:29.980 --> 22:32.949
I PROMISE YOU NOT ONE OF THEM
IS COMING OUT TODAY.
(cell phone beeps)

22:32.980 --> 22:35.540
(line rings)
THOSE OFFICERS ARE
AT THE STATION,

22:35.580 --> 22:37.047
AND THEY ARE NOT
GOING ANYWHERE.

22:37.080 --> 22:38.081
(man)
9-1-1. What's your emergen--

22:38.120 --> 22:40.509
(beeps and clatters)

22:40.560 --> 22:42.812
DON'T WORRY.
THEY'RE COMIN' FOR YA.

22:42.860 --> 22:44.657
WON'T BE LONG.

22:44.690 --> 22:46.453
KEVIN?

22:48.000 --> 22:50.127
KEVIN !

22:52.430 --> 22:53.931
(siren wailing)

22:53.970 --> 22:55.835
WE ALREADY HAVE EYES
ON THE BUILDING.

22:55.870 --> 22:57.462
TWO FLOORS, SILENT ENTRY.

22:57.510 --> 23:00.570
ASSAULT TEAMS WILL BE STATIONED
ON THE SOUTHEAST

23:00.610 --> 23:01.770
AND NORTHWEST CORNERS.

23:01.810 --> 23:04.699
HEY. WE JUST PICKED UP A SIGNAL
FROM OLIVER'S CELL PHONE.

23:04.750 --> 23:06.775
SAME LOCATION.
ST. AUGUSTUS ON QUEEN.

23:06.810 --> 23:09.973
OKAY, BAILEY, CALLAGHAN,
YOU'LL BE RUNNING THIS

23:10.020 --> 23:10.839
FROM THE COMMAND BUS.

23:10.890 --> 23:12.812
I WANT ALL CLEARED OFFICERS
ON THIS.

23:12.850 --> 23:14.056
WE DON'T KNOW WHAT WE'RE
WALKING INTO HERE,

23:14.090 --> 23:15.682
SO LET'S KEEP OUR EYES OPEN.
THAT CLEAR?

23:15.720 --> 23:17.051
(officers) YES, SIR.
EVERYONE COMES HOME TODAY.

23:17.090 --> 23:19.888
EVERY SINGLE ONE OF YOU.
NASH, YOU'RE WITH CALLAGHAN.

23:19.930 --> 23:21.921
MCNALLY, COLLINS, SWAREK,
YOU'RE STAYING PUT.

23:21.960 --> 23:23.996
NO DISCUSSION.

23:24.030 --> 23:27.466
(indistinct conversations)

23:27.500 --> 23:28.592
I KNOW.

23:31.740 --> 23:34.038
I DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD GO.

23:34.080 --> 23:36.105
STEVE, IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

23:36.140 --> 23:39.644
YOU KNOW, YOU STAY
AT THE BACK, ALL RIGHT?

23:39.680 --> 23:42.649
YOU GO IN LAST.
YOU ACT LIKE A COWARD.

23:42.680 --> 23:44.489
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

23:44.520 --> 23:45.885
COWARDICE IS
HIGHLY UNDERRATED, TRACI.

23:45.920 --> 23:46.909
THE THING IS,
YOU WOULD KNOW THAT

23:46.950 --> 23:48.884
SINCE YOU HAPPEN TO BE
THE TOUGHEST BROAD I KNOW,

23:48.920 --> 23:50.182
AND THAT'S SAYING A LOT,

23:50.220 --> 23:52.723
CONSIDERING I GREW UP
WITH GAIL, YOU KNOW.

23:56.900 --> 23:59.164
HOW ABOUT I MAKE YOU
THAT DINNER TONIGHT?

23:59.200 --> 24:01.589
I'D LIKE THAT, BUT, UH,

24:01.640 --> 24:02.959
RED WINE FOR
THE LITTLE GUY, RIGHT?

24:03.000 --> 24:05.139
YEAH, SOMETHING LIKE THAT.
YEAH?

24:05.170 --> 24:06.137
(whispers) CAREFUL.

24:06.170 --> 24:08.707
(whispers) SEE YOU SOON.

24:08.740 --> 24:11.470
HAVE YOU CALLED HOLLY?
EXCUSE ME?

24:11.510 --> 24:13.239
LOOK, I CALLED MY MOM,
CHRISTIAN.

24:13.280 --> 24:14.872
HELL, I EVEN TALKED
TO DENISE.

24:14.920 --> 24:16.069
I'M LUCKY THAT EVERYONE ELSE
I CARE ABOUT

24:16.120 --> 24:18.588
IS RIGHT HERE AT THIS DIVISION.

24:18.620 --> 24:22.989
GAIL, I'M JUST SAYING...
CALL HER.

24:24.260 --> 24:26.854
HEY, KEVIN, LISTEN TO ME, MAN.

24:26.890 --> 24:30.155
IT'S NOT TOO LATE.
YOU GOT--YOU GOT TIME STILL.

24:30.200 --> 24:32.566
YOU GOT MY RADIO.
JUST HIT THE BUTTON ON THE SIDE

24:32.600 --> 24:35.034
AND TELL 'EM THAT IT'S OVER.

24:37.240 --> 24:40.505
(radio chatter)
SNIPER ON THE SOUTH SIDE.
CAN'T SEE ANYTHING.

24:40.540 --> 24:42.235
NOTHING FROM
THE MAIN ENTRANCEWAY.

24:42.280 --> 24:43.269
NO MOVEMENT INSIDE.

24:43.310 --> 24:45.642
(radio static)
I WANT EYES
INSIDE THE BUILDING.

24:45.680 --> 24:47.238
(man) Copy that.
Heading to the south end.

24:47.280 --> 24:51.148
I MEAN, WHAT DO YOU THINK'S
GONNA ACTUALLY HAPPEN HERE?

24:51.190 --> 24:53.112
IT'S JUST YOU AND ME, MAN.
THERE IS NO E.T.F.

24:53.150 --> 24:54.856
I LIED ABOUT THAT.

24:54.890 --> 24:57.779
SORRY TO BURST YOUR BUBBLE.
I AM NOT THAT IMPORTANT A GUY.

25:00.230 --> 25:02.926
(radio chatter)

25:02.960 --> 25:04.291
(man) Okay.

25:04.330 --> 25:06.696
KEVIN, THEY'RE HERE!
E.T.F. IS HERE! I LIED, MAN!

25:06.730 --> 25:08.038
YOU GOT ABOUT TWO MINUTES!

25:08.070 --> 25:09.992
(radio chatter)

25:10.040 --> 25:12.258
HE'S ALIVE.

25:12.310 --> 25:13.265
KEVIN, IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

25:13.310 --> 25:15.608
I SWEAR TO GOD,
I'LL MAKE THIS RIGHT FOR YOU.

25:15.640 --> 25:16.800
IF YOU DIDN'T DO IT...

25:16.840 --> 25:19.149
(video audio muted)

25:19.180 --> 25:22.115
(siren wailing in distance)

25:24.220 --> 25:25.710
(Oliver) YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
To PUT YOUR GUN DOWN, MAN.

25:25.750 --> 25:28.878
THIS IS YOUR ONLY CHANCE.
COME OUT, COME OUT.

25:28.920 --> 25:31.252
IT ISN'T WORTH IT, MY FRIEND,
I SWEAR.

25:31.290 --> 25:33.178
YOU CAN WORK THIS OUT.
YOU CAN FIGURE IT OUT...

25:33.230 --> 25:35.994
(siren wailing in distance)

25:36.030 --> 25:37.099
(radio static)
(man) Southwest door
barricaded shut.

25:37.130 --> 25:38.722
Looks like some kind
of pressure switch, pipe bomb.

25:38.770 --> 25:40.021
(radio static)

25:40.070 --> 25:42.061
(man) Same thing on our side.
No entry at the southeast door.

25:42.100 --> 25:44.068
Only clear entrwNay
is north door.

25:44.110 --> 25:46.260
THEN WE GO THROUGH
THE FRONT.

25:46.310 --> 25:49.871
ALPHA, BRAVO, MOVE TO NORTH SIDE
FOR IMMEDIATE ENTRY.

25:49.910 --> 25:51.707
(radio static)
Roger that.

26:05.860 --> 26:06.827
Taking the west staircase.

26:06.860 --> 26:07.895
Roger that.
Taking the east.

26:11.770 --> 26:14.762
NO, NO! GO BACK! GO BACK!
THERE'S A GUN!

26:14.800 --> 26:16.165
GUN! GUN IN THE BALCONY!

26:20.010 --> 26:22.274
WEST BALCONY CLEAR!

26:22.310 --> 26:24.778
CENTER'S CLEAR.
EAST BALCONY CLEAR!

26:24.810 --> 26:27.244
GOT A RIFLE ON THE EAST BALCONY.

26:27.280 --> 26:29.840
WE'RE CLEAR!
GOING IN THREE.

26:29.880 --> 26:31.040
(clacking)
(grunts)

26:33.050 --> 26:34.950
HEY, HEY!

26:34.990 --> 26:38.084
(groaning)

26:38.130 --> 26:40.792
FRANKIE?
GOOD TO SEE YOU, BROTHER.

26:40.830 --> 26:41.797
YEAH, YOU SHOULD LISTEN.
GET HIM OUTTA HERE.

26:41.830 --> 26:42.649
GUY WAS RIGHT UP THERE.

26:42.700 --> 26:43.724
I THOUGHT HE WAS
GONNA START SHOOTING.

26:43.770 --> 26:45.692
HE WAS UP ON THE BALCONY.
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

26:45.730 --> 26:49.359
(radio chatter)

26:49.400 --> 26:52.130
(man speaks indistinctly)

26:59.180 --> 27:00.169
I COULDN'T GET AHOLD
OF HER PARENTS,

27:00.210 --> 27:01.711
BUT I CALLED MY DAD.
HE'S A DOCTOR,

27:01.750 --> 27:03.843
SO, YOU KNOW, I FIGURED
WE'D GET A SECOND OPINION.

27:03.890 --> 27:05.812
I-I EXPLAINED EVERYTHING
TO HIM,

27:05.850 --> 27:09.217
AND HE THINKS THAT SURGERY
IS DEFINITELY HER BEST OPTION.

27:09.260 --> 27:11.251
(scoffs)

27:11.290 --> 27:13.690
I CAN'T LET THEM CUT HER OPEN
AGAIN, MAN. NOT NOW.

27:13.730 --> 27:15.288
I KNOW, BUT IF WE DON'T
DO THIS OPERATION,

27:15.330 --> 27:17.252
SHE COULD BE PARALYZED
OR WORSE.

27:17.300 --> 27:19.029
THAT COULD HAPPEN
IF THEY DO OPERATE.

27:19.070 --> 27:21.288
BUT THE DOCTOR SAID
IT'S FAR LESS LIKELY.

27:21.340 --> 27:23.399
SHE ALSO SAID
CHLOE COULD HEAL ON HER OWN.

27:23.440 --> 27:24.429
SO WHAT,
YOU WANNA JUST DO NOTHING?

27:24.470 --> 27:26.404
YOU WANNA JUST GAMBLE
THAT SHE'S GONNA BE OKAY?

27:26.440 --> 27:29.329
LOOK, I DON'T NEED
YOUR PERMISSION HERE.

27:29.380 --> 27:32.872
I'M HER HUSBAND. I HAVE
THE AUTHORITY TO MAKE THIS CALL.

27:32.910 --> 27:35.947
SO THAT'S IT?

27:35.980 --> 27:37.743
THIS IS WHAT SHE'D WANT.

27:37.790 --> 27:38.916
AND IF YOU KNEW HER
AS WELL AS YOU THINK YOU DO,

27:38.950 --> 27:40.144
YOU'D KNOW THAT.

27:40.190 --> 27:41.919
I'M GETTING THE DOCTOR.

27:41.960 --> 27:44.929
SHE NEEDS TO HAVE
THIS OPERATION.

27:44.960 --> 27:46.427
DOV.

27:46.460 --> 27:47.529
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

27:51.470 --> 27:54.030
OLIVER'S OKAY. THEY FOUND HIM.
HE WAS AT THE CHURCH.

27:54.070 --> 27:55.890
WHERE'S FORD?
DID THEY BRING HIM IN?

27:55.940 --> 27:57.293
THEY DIDN'T FIND FORD.

27:57.340 --> 27:59.103
WHAT?
HE WASN'T AT THE CHURCH.

27:59.140 --> 28:01.028
I DON'T KNOW. WE GOT
OFFICERS AT HIS HOUSE,

28:01.080 --> 28:03.207
AT THE WAREHOUSE,
AT HIS BROTHER'S CABIN.

28:03.240 --> 28:04.377
HE'S NOT GONNA GO THERE.

28:04.410 --> 28:05.946
HE USED IT AS HIS ALIBI
LAST TIME,

28:05.980 --> 28:06.969
AND IT DIDN'T ADD UP THEN.

28:07.010 --> 28:08.079
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

28:08.120 --> 28:10.270
HIS BROTHER SAID THAT THEY
SPENT THE WEEKEND TOGETHER.

28:10.320 --> 28:12.345
BUT THERE'S NO EVIDENCE
OF IT.

28:12.390 --> 28:15.416
OKAY? I HAVE
A WITNESS STATEMENT...

28:15.460 --> 28:18.020
THAT SAYS, "NO,
I DID NOT SEE KEVIN'S VAN.

28:18.060 --> 28:20.324
IN FACT, I DIDN'T SEE
ANY VEHICLES AT ALL.

28:20.360 --> 28:22.021
MAYBE NEITHER ONE OF THEM
WAS THERE.

28:22.060 --> 28:25.063
WELL, ABE SAID THAT THEY WERE,
SO WHY WOULD HE LIE ABOUT THAT?

28:25.100 --> 28:26.829
I DON'T KNOW.

28:26.870 --> 28:28.269
(radio chatter)

28:28.300 --> 28:31.007
MAKE AN ALIBI
FOR HIS BROTHER?

28:31.040 --> 28:33.361
(door buzzes in distance)

28:44.350 --> 28:46.818
WHAT IF I WAS WRONG?

28:46.850 --> 28:48.078
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

28:48.120 --> 28:52.955
THIS WHOLE TIME, WHAT IF I WAS
LOOKING AT THE WRONG BROTHER?

28:52.990 --> 28:54.924
(gun clicks)

28:54.960 --> 28:56.097
HEY.

28:56.130 --> 28:57.290
HEY.

28:57.330 --> 28:58.422
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

28:58.470 --> 28:59.892
GOING HOME.

28:59.930 --> 29:01.989
THE GUY'S STILL OUT THERE.

29:02.040 --> 29:05.430
(chuckles) YEAH. I KNOW.

29:05.470 --> 29:06.505
YOU SHOULD STAY HERE.

29:06.540 --> 29:09.100
FRANK'S RIGHT.

29:09.140 --> 29:10.107
BEST PLACE FOR YOU.

29:10.140 --> 29:12.142
OH. BUT NOT YOU,
RIGHT?

29:12.180 --> 29:15.843
YOU'RE GOOD.
YOU'RE BULLETPROOF.

29:15.880 --> 29:16.847
NO.

29:16.880 --> 29:17.915
SAM, YOU CAN'T JUST LEAVE.

29:17.950 --> 29:19.508
YEAH, I CAN, ACTUALLY.

29:19.550 --> 29:22.053
IT'S THE ONLY THING
I CAN DO.

29:22.090 --> 29:24.024
THE ONLY GOOD THING.

29:24.060 --> 29:27.223
HEY. HEY! WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
THE ONLY GOOD THING YOU CAN DO?

29:27.260 --> 29:28.352
HOW'S IT A GOOD THING
TO LEAVE?

29:28.400 --> 29:30.356
EVERYBODY'S FINE.
OLIVER'S OKAY.

29:30.400 --> 29:32.322
RIGHT. SO STAY.
I CAN'T.

29:32.370 --> 29:34.429
I CAN'T. (sighs)

29:34.470 --> 29:36.335
(man speaks indistinctly)

29:36.370 --> 29:40.204
I CAN'T BE HERE ANYMORE...
WITH YOU.

29:40.240 --> 29:42.105
I... I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

29:42.140 --> 29:44.449
I SCREWED IT UP.
IT'S MY FAULT.

29:44.480 --> 29:47.347
I SCREWED IT UP
OVER AND OVER AND OVER AGAIN.

29:47.380 --> 29:50.144
ANDY, I WANT YOU
TO BE HAPPY,

29:50.180 --> 29:51.442
MORE THAN ANYTHING
IN THE WORLD,

29:51.490 --> 29:54.550
MORE THAN ANYTHING
I COULD EVER WANT FOR MYSELF.

29:54.590 --> 29:56.808
AND YOU ARE--WITH HIM.

29:56.860 --> 30:00.079
AND THAT MEANS, UH...

30:02.000 --> 30:03.149
I GOTTA GO.

30:07.130 --> 30:09.462
SAM. HEY.

30:11.510 --> 30:12.568
SAM.

30:12.610 --> 30:14.237
(horn honks in distance)

30:14.280 --> 30:15.531
SAM.

30:15.580 --> 30:18.242
1504--THIS IS OLIVER'S SQUAD.

30:18.280 --> 30:20.168
WHY IS IT HERE?

30:23.480 --> 30:24.811
(clicks)

30:28.260 --> 30:29.989
(beeps)

30:30.020 --> 30:32.853
(indistinct conversations)
(Frank) YEAH? WHAT'S GOING ON?

30:32.890 --> 30:34.152
MCNALLY AND I
ARE IN THE PARKING LOT.

30:34.200 --> 30:35.997
WE GOT OLIVER'S CRUISER.
Swarek...

30:36.030 --> 30:37.429
I TOLD YOU TO STAY
IN THE STATION.

30:37.460 --> 30:38.563
YEAH, I KNOW.

30:38.600 --> 30:40.989
LISTEN,
EVERYONE ON THE LIST IS HERE,

30:41.040 --> 30:43.497
AND NOW OLIVER'S CAR
IS PARKED OUTSIDE.

30:43.540 --> 30:46.464
WAIT, WAIT. THAT CAN'T BE.
WE HAVE NOT RECOVERED HIS SQUAD.

30:46.510 --> 30:48.535
I THINK HE'S HERE.
THIS WHOLE THING IS A DIVERSION.

30:48.580 --> 30:50.901
I THINK KEVIN FORD
IS IN THE STATION.

30:50.950 --> 30:52.349
SWAREK. SWAREK!

30:52.380 --> 30:54.109
(door buzzes and beeps)

30:54.150 --> 30:56.038
WHAT'S GOING ON?

30:56.080 --> 30:56.910
(lowered voice)
WE HAVE REASON TO BELIEVE

30:56.950 --> 30:58.508
KEVIN FORD IS IN THE BUILDING,
ARMED.

30:58.550 --> 31:00.347
YOU NEED TO SECURE THIS AREA.

31:00.390 --> 31:01.618
I'VE GOT FOUR BODIES
IN CELLS.

31:01.660 --> 31:03.309
HE'S NOT AFTER THEM.
HE'S AFTER US.

31:03.360 --> 31:05.157
LOCK THE DOORS AND DON'T LET
ANYONE IN YOU DON'T RECOGNIZE.

31:05.190 --> 31:07.351
FORD MIGHT BE WEARING
A POLICE UNIFORM.

31:07.390 --> 31:08.527
I'LL START CLEARING
FROM HERE,

31:08.560 --> 31:10.323
THEN I'M GETTING MY GUN.
YOU STAY PUT.

31:10.360 --> 31:13.193
I'M GONNA CLEAR THE SQUAD ROOM,
AND I'LL MEET YOU IN THE MIDDLE.

31:13.230 --> 31:16.199
(radio chatter)

31:30.320 --> 31:32.140
(turns knob)

31:33.620 --> 31:36.589
(radio chatter continues)

32:23.600 --> 32:25.204
(telephone rings)

32:25.240 --> 32:28.073
(indistinct conversations,
radio chatter)

32:33.550 --> 32:35.040
CELERY.

32:35.080 --> 32:37.219
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
I'M ON MY WAY TO THE HOSPITAL.

32:37.250 --> 32:38.512
IS OLIVER OKAY?
OLIVER'S FINE.

32:38.550 --> 32:39.744
I THINK KEVIN FORD
IS IN THE BUILDING,

32:39.790 --> 32:40.745
DRESSED AS A POLICE OFFICER.

32:40.790 --> 32:43.611
COME WITH ME. LOCK IT DOWN.
STAY OFF THE RADIO.

32:43.660 --> 32:44.729
RIGHT. I GOT IT.

32:44.760 --> 32:46.421
WHAT IS YOUR NAME?

32:46.460 --> 32:48.098
WENDY.
OKAY, WENDY, COME WITH ME.

32:48.130 --> 32:49.154
IN HERE, PLEASE.

32:49.200 --> 32:50.758
WH-WHAT'S HAPPENING?

32:50.800 --> 32:51.869
STAY HERE.
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,

32:51.900 --> 32:54.130
DO NOT OPEN THE DOOR
UNLESS YOU RECOGNIZE THE VOICE

32:54.170 --> 32:55.569
ON THE OTHER SIDE.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

32:55.600 --> 32:57.966
(radio chatter)

33:01.810 --> 33:03.107
(unholsters gun)

33:05.610 --> 33:07.339
SAY KEVIN HAS
A WEEKEND BLACKOUT.

33:07.380 --> 33:08.415
HE DOESN'T HAVE
A SOLID ALIBI

33:08.450 --> 33:09.542
WHEN THE POLICE COME ASKING
ABOUT THE HARTLEY BOY,

33:09.580 --> 33:13.141
SO ABE OFFERS TO HELP.

33:13.190 --> 33:15.658
BUILDS HIMSELF AN ALIBI
IN THE PROCESS.

33:15.690 --> 33:18.352
AND HE PINS IT ALL
ON HIS LITTLE BROTHER.

33:18.390 --> 33:20.085
ABE'S STILL
IN THE STATION, RIGHT?

33:20.130 --> 33:22.519
I THINK SO.

33:27.530 --> 33:28.758
(vibrating)

33:33.770 --> 33:35.772
COLLINS.

33:35.810 --> 33:38.040
FORD! NO!

33:42.120 --> 33:44.088
(Officers shouting at once)

33:44.120 --> 33:45.348
SAM !

33:45.390 --> 33:46.743
(door buzzes and beeps)

33:46.790 --> 33:49.554
(shouting continues,
radio chatter)

33:49.590 --> 33:50.352
YOU GOTTA
KEEP YOUR HEAD DOWN.

33:50.390 --> 33:52.119
STAY DOWN, STAY DOWN.
NO, NO, NO.

33:52.160 --> 33:53.184
SAM, YOU GOTTA STAY DOWN,
OKAY?

33:53.230 --> 33:55.198
(indistinct Shouting continues)

33:55.230 --> 33:58.097
WE GOT HIM.

33:58.130 --> 33:59.825
WE DID.

33:59.870 --> 34:01.360
TOLD YOU WE WOULD.

34:01.400 --> 34:03.493
I MEAN, I DIDN'T MEAN
I TOLD YOU SO, BUT...

34:03.540 --> 34:05.098
(panﬁng)
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEANT.

34:05.140 --> 34:06.266
I GOTTA GET UP.

34:06.310 --> 34:07.504
SAM, NO,
YOU GOTTA STAY DOWN, PLEASE.
I GOTTA GET UP.

34:07.540 --> 34:09.428
SAM, PLEASE,
YOU GOTTA RELAX, OKAY?

34:09.480 --> 34:10.799
JUST STAY DOWN.
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

34:13.210 --> 34:15.815
(indistinct Shouting)

34:15.850 --> 34:18.080
MOVE. OFFICER,
YOU GOTTA MOVE BACK.

34:18.120 --> 34:20.088
NO, I'M GOING.

34:22.620 --> 34:24.781
(gurney wheels clack)

34:24.830 --> 34:27.390
(siren wailing)

34:27.430 --> 34:31.366
(indistinct conversations)

34:31.400 --> 34:34.198
(siren continues wailing)

34:34.240 --> 34:38.267
(ventilator whooshing)

34:38.310 --> 34:40.733
C.T.A.S. 1.
WE HAVE A 35-YEAR-OLD MALE.

34:40.770 --> 34:42.874
P.O., G.S.W. TO THE CHEST.

34:42.910 --> 34:44.138
G.C.S.'s A 9.

34:44.180 --> 34:45.147
SAM?
FIVE MINUTES OUT.

34:45.180 --> 34:46.807
I'M RIGHT HERE.

34:46.850 --> 34:49.842
(strained voice) OKAY.

34:49.880 --> 34:53.247
I'M JUST GONNA...
TALK OR SOMETHING

34:53.290 --> 34:54.552
UNTIL WE GET THERE,
'CAUSE I DON'T REALLY KNOW

34:54.590 --> 34:56.512
WHAT ELSE TO DO.

34:56.560 --> 34:57.458
OKAY.
SO...

34:57.490 --> 35:01.824
OKAY, BUT NOT YOU.
OKAY? SAVE EVERY BREATH.

35:01.860 --> 35:03.657
GOOD PLAN.

35:03.700 --> 35:05.895
IT IS, ACTUALLY.

35:05.930 --> 35:07.488
IT'S AN EXCELLENT PLAN.

35:07.530 --> 35:10.636
YOU'RE GONNA LIE THERE,
AND YOU'RE GONNA LISTEN TO ME.

35:10.670 --> 35:14.276
I'M GONNA TELL YOU
A STORY.

35:14.310 --> 35:16.505
IT WAS JUST, YOU KNOW,
A NORMAL NIGHT,

35:16.540 --> 35:20.772
AND WE WERE LYING IN BED.
AND...

35:20.810 --> 35:22.744
MY STOMACH WAS HURTING
FROM LAUGHING

35:22.780 --> 35:24.919
'CAUSE YOU WERE TEASING ME
ABOUT SOMETHING.

35:24.950 --> 35:26.918
I DON'T REMEMBER WHAT.

35:26.950 --> 35:29.384
I MUST HAVE FALLEN ASLEEP
OR SOMETHING,

35:29.420 --> 35:34.289
BECAUSE... ALL OF A SUDDEN
I WAS HAVING THIS--

35:34.330 --> 35:36.298
THIS REALLY TERRIBLE DREAM.

35:37.900 --> 35:39.663
AND I COULDN'T STOP CRYING.

35:39.700 --> 35:41.565
YOU KNOW,
I WAS CRYING AND...

35:44.940 --> 35:47.431
YOU WEREN'T EVEN
REALLY AWAKE.

35:50.510 --> 35:53.445
I REMEMBER YOU--
YOU GRABBED ME.

35:53.480 --> 35:54.777
I REMEMBER...

35:54.820 --> 35:56.549
YOU WERE JUST HOLDING ME
SO TIGHT,

35:56.580 --> 35:58.514
ALL OF A SUDDEN,

35:58.550 --> 36:02.384
YOU SAID,
"I'M RIGHT HERE.

36:02.420 --> 36:05.184
I'M GONNA HOLD ON TO YOU,
AND I'M NEVER GONNA LET YOU GO."

36:05.230 --> 36:08.893
RIGHT THEN...

36:08.930 --> 36:12.718
I KNEW THAT I WOULD NEVER
FEEL MORE LOVED...

36:15.440 --> 36:17.897
(voice breaks)
OR MORE KNOWN.

36:17.940 --> 36:19.703
LOOK, I KNOW IT'S SMALL.

36:19.740 --> 36:21.230
I KNOW
IT'S A REALLY SMALL MOMENT.

36:21.280 --> 36:24.306
IT'S... IT'S NOT
EVEN A GOOD STORY.

36:24.350 --> 36:26.568
THAT WAS
A PRETTY GOOD STORY.

36:26.610 --> 36:29.613
I LOVE YOU.

36:29.650 --> 36:31.174
I LOVE YOU.

36:33.020 --> 36:35.750
YOU'RE MY STORY.

36:35.790 --> 36:37.417
SAM...

36:37.460 --> 36:38.688
YOU.

36:38.730 --> 36:42.393
(swallows)

36:48.030 --> 36:50.567
OFFICER, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO MOVE BACK.

36:50.600 --> 36:54.809
(siren wailing in distance)

37:10.520 --> 37:12.829
(monitor beeping steadily)

37:16.030 --> 37:17.452
SO?

37:17.500 --> 37:19.821
HE WON'T CONSENT
TO THE PROCEDURE.

37:19.870 --> 37:21.667
OKAY, BUT MAYBE IF WE
TALK TO HIM TOGETHER...

37:21.700 --> 37:23.031
NO, YOU CAN'T GO IN THERE.

37:23.070 --> 37:24.264
WHAT?

37:24.310 --> 37:25.834
HE'S MADE HIS WISHES CLEAR,

37:25.870 --> 37:28.907
AND NOW HE'S ASKED TO BE
ALONE WITH HIS WIFE.

37:28.940 --> 37:30.009
I'M SORRY.

37:31.850 --> 37:34.819
(Matt Walters'
"I Would Die For You" playing)

37:53.600 --> 37:54.862
(door buzzes and beeps)

37:56.340 --> 37:57.898
ANY NEWS?

37:57.940 --> 37:59.737
YEAH. THEY'RE MOVING HIM
INTO SURGERY.

37:59.770 --> 38:03.069
* HE BURIED HER HEART STILL

38:03.110 --> 38:05.544
LOOK, MARLO. ..

38:05.580 --> 38:09.676
EVERYTHING THAT'S HAPPENED
HERE WITH YOU...

38:09.720 --> 38:10.948
WE NEED TO DEAL WITH IT.

38:10.980 --> 38:13.380
YEAH.

38:13.420 --> 38:14.580
I GOT IT.

38:14.620 --> 38:16.349
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO PACK YOUR THINGS.

38:16.390 --> 38:17.687
GO HOME.

38:17.720 --> 38:19.756
MM-HMM.

38:19.790 --> 38:20.757
TAKE YOUR TIME.

38:20.790 --> 38:22.826
* IN THE RAINED-ON RIVERBED

38:22.860 --> 38:24.464
(door buzzes and beeps)

38:28.540 --> 38:30.690
IS HE ALIVE?

38:30.740 --> 38:31.832
NO.

38:31.870 --> 38:33.929
NO, HE'S NOT.

38:33.970 --> 38:37.076
LOOK, ABE, I'M GONNA...
HAVE TO ASK YOU

38:37.110 --> 38:39.943
ABOUT MARCUS HARTLEY.

38:39.980 --> 38:42.915
COME ON, DETECTIVE.
IT'S OVER.

38:42.950 --> 38:45.009
JUST HELP ME CLEAR UP
A FEW THINGS.

38:45.050 --> 38:47.086
THE WEEKEND
THAT MARCUS DISAPPEARED,

38:47.120 --> 38:49.486
WHERE WERE YOU?

38:49.520 --> 38:51.886
* HE COULD FEEL HER FLOAT

38:57.400 --> 39:00.961
* SHE SAID, "I...

39:01.000 --> 39:04.868
* "I WOULD DIE FOR YOU

39:04.910 --> 39:08.004
* "AND I

39:08.040 --> 39:10.429
* I WOULD DIE FOR YOU"

39:10.480 --> 39:12.004
HEY, I CAME
AS SOON AS I HEARD.

39:12.050 --> 39:14.871
HEY.

39:14.920 --> 39:16.911
I'M REALLY GLAD
THAT YOU'RE HERE.

39:20.590 --> 39:22.854
STEVE, THIS IS HOLLY.
CHRIS, THIS IS HOLLY.

39:22.890 --> 39:24.016
HEY, HOW'S IT GOING?

39:24.060 --> 39:26.528
HEY.

39:30.030 --> 39:31.019
(whispers)
WAKE UP, WAKE UP.

39:31.060 --> 39:32.163
YOU GOTTA WAKE UP.

39:32.200 --> 39:33.997
* A LOVE SO DARK

39:34.030 --> 39:36.169
COME ON, BABY.
YOU GOTTA STOP WAKING ME UP.

39:36.200 --> 39:38.430
YOU GOTTA WAKE UP
EVERY HOUR.
(groans)

39:38.470 --> 39:40.631
IT'S BEEN FIVE MINUTES.

39:40.670 --> 39:43.104
NO, IT HASN'T, DUMBO.

39:43.140 --> 39:44.744
(chuckles)
(whispers) EYES OPEN.

39:44.780 --> 39:48.671
HEY, WHAT, UH, OKAY.
IS IT, UH...

39:48.720 --> 39:49.812
(whispers) WHAT?
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

39:49.850 --> 39:50.976
OKAY, DID WE GET HIM?

39:51.020 --> 39:52.510
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
WE GOT HIM.

39:52.550 --> 39:53.812
YEAH?
YOU GOT HIM, YEAH.

39:53.850 --> 39:56.614
OKAY, GOOD. GOOD. YEAH.
SO EVERYTHING...

39:56.660 --> 39:57.615
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

39:57.660 --> 40:00.424
YEAH, EVERYTHING'S FINE.

40:00.460 --> 40:02.553
OKAY.

40:02.600 --> 40:04.522
GOOD.

40:04.570 --> 40:07.198
MM.
